rComments: Read pretty much straight off the slides. Had an annoying tendency to read equations out (equations with subscripts and all that are better seen than heard). Was incredibly unclear in explaining non-intuitive quantum physics concepts. Honestly that's all I can say - for a QM course, you would expect understandable explanations for wonky concepts...

He's a good lecturer. He does follow the book quite a lot, but he also highlights the things from the book that are important. He's approachable and helpful. The only thing I didn't like was that the course was a little too easy for my taste and I think he could've fit in a little more physics if he went at a slightly faster pace.
Good at lecturing. Always ready to help. Good prof overall
Boring...time to change the channel...at least that's how I felt to the 10 or so of his lectures I actually went to. Even his jokes were from the textbook.
Pretty good at lecturing. Fair tests/assignments. It was a nice course...
Going to his class was just storytelling time: he just read out the textbook. Nevertheless, he will help you outside of class (or he will try to help you)
Every single word was almost read from the book...no use of lectures...at least the book (Griffith) was good...although he is a nice guy...
